===Noun===
'''hawberk''' (''plural'' hawberks)
#(''Armor'') [[Category:Armor]] A [[hauberk]]. A coat of [[mail]]; especially, the long coat of mail of the European Middle Ages, as contrasted with the [[habergeon]], which is shorter and sometimes [[sleeveless]].
#:'''Quotations'''
#:*'''1786''': The [[hawberk]] and [[haubergeon]] long continued almost the [[sole]] [[defensive]] [[armour]] of this country...  &mdash; Francis Grose, ''A Treatise on Ancient Armour and Weapons'', page 73.